{"questionId":"6969","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>3.26 g of iron powder are added to 80.0 cm<sup>3</sup> of 0.200 mol dm<sup>−3</sup> copper(II) sulfate solution. The following reaction occurs:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\">Fe (s) + CuSO<sub>4</sub> (aq) → FeSO<sub>4</sub> (aq) + Cu (s)</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>The only significant uncertainty is in the temperature measurement.</p>\n<p>Determine the absolute uncertainty in the calculated value of Δ<em>H</em> if the uncertainty in the temperature rise was ±0.2 °C.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em><strong>ALTERNATIVE 1:</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>«</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0.2\\,^\\circ {\\text{C}} \\times \\frac{{100}}{{7.5\\,^\\circ {\\text{C}}}} = \">\n  <mn>0.2</mn>\n  <msup>\n    <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n    <mo>∘</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>C</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>100</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>7.5</mn>\n      <msup>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n        <mo>∘</mo>\n      </msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>C</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n</math></span><strong>»</strong> 3 %/0.03&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p><strong>«</strong>0.03 × 160 kJ<strong>»</strong> =&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>±<strong>»</strong> 5 <strong>«</strong>kJ<strong>»&nbsp;</strong>✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>ALTERNATIVE 2:</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>«</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0.2\\,^\\circ {\\text{C}} \\times \\frac{{100}}{{7.5\\,^\\circ {\\text{C}}}} = \">\n  <mn>0.2</mn>\n  <msup>\n    <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n    <mo>∘</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>C</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>100</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>7.5</mn>\n      <msup>\n        <msp